message.text:
"Evangelion and Japanese Swords" Paris Exhibition is getting ready for 4/30 opening!
Japanese swordsmiths have set up the swords together with staff members in Paris.
Be the witness of this epoch‐making collaboration between "Eva" and "Japanese swords" －Japanese NEW and TRADITIONAL art! #evangelion #Japanesesword
ヱヴァンゲリヲンと日本刀展、4/30からの開催に向け、準備も大詰め！刀剣職人さんが日本から渡仏して、パリの方々と一緒に刀剣作品の設営を行いました♪
「ヱヴァ」×「日本刀」の斬新なコラボを通じて、今までにない新しい日本文化の可能性をお届けします！
http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/culture/new/1401/01-01.html
http://www.mcjp.fr/francais/expositions/evangelion-et-les-sabres-japonais-979/evangelion-et-les-sabres-japonais

message.text:
France: Apr.30 Demonstration of Japanese Sword Engraving 
フランス：4/30 刀身彫刻デモンストレーション

"Evangelion and Japanese Sword" Exhibition is coming soon! 
Tell us your favorite "SWORD"! SAKABATO? TESSAIGA? WADO ICHIMONJI? 

Japanese swords are often etched with beautiful engraving on the blades. Depending on the ways of combat and time trends, the patterns present practical, religious or decorative features of that specific age. Mr. Munenori Kinoshita, one of the few sword engravers still remaining in Japan today, will show this incredible ancient skill live. 

http://www.mcjp.fr/francais/conferences-6/la-gravure-sur-lame-de-sabre-991/la-gravure-sur-lame-de-sabre

もうすぐ開催の「ヱヴァンゲリヲンと日本刀展」にあわせ、日本に数人しかいない刀身彫刻師・木下宗憲氏によるデモンストレーションを実施！あなたの好きな「刀」は？逆刃刀？鉄砕牙？和道一文字？
(C)All Japan Swordsmith Association Operation Department

message.text:
Today is "Day of Letter"! In Japan, every 23rd of the month is called fumi no hi, Day of Letter. “23” is read as fu (２) mi (３) in Japanese that together sound the same as fumi(文) meaning "letter". Have you written a letter recently? Why don't you write one today!
毎月２３日は「ふみの日」！今日は手紙を書いてみませんか？
http://words.marugotoweb.jp/search_keyword.php?q=てがみ&lang=en
